        "identifier": "main.money_stg.vw_deposit",
        "description": [
          "This is the central source of truth for all Global Deposits. It tracks successful funding events across various company platforms, including the IBAN and Trading platforms. Each row represents a single deposit transaction. Use this table for analyzing deposit volume, frequency, and platform-specific performance\n"
        ],
        "column_configs": [
          {
            "column_name": "AccountType",
            "description": [
              "The specific platform receiving the funds (e.g., 'Trading', 'IBAN'). Use this to compare performance between different product offerings."
            ],
            "enable_format_assistance": true,
            "enable_entity_matching": true
          },
          {
            "column_name": "AmountInUSD",
            "description": [
              "The gross value of the deposit converted to USD. This column is 100% populated. Always sum this for \"Total Deposit Volume.\""
            ],
            "enable_format_assistance": true
          },
          {
            "column_name": "Country",
            "description": [
              "The customer's country of residence at the time of the transaction.\n"
            ],
            "enable_format_assistance": true,
            "enable_entity_matching": true
          },
          {
            "column_name": "Date",
            "description": [
              "The primary timestamp for the transaction. Use this for daily, monthly, or yearly deposit trends."
            ],
            "enable_format_assistance": true
          },
          {
            "column_name": "FundingType",
            "description": [
              "The payment method used for the deposit (e.g., Credit Card, Wire Transfer, E-wallet)."
            ],
            "enable_format_assistance": true,
            "enable_entity_matching": true
          },
          {
            "column_name": "GCID",
            "description": [
              "Global Customer Identifier. A single GCID can have multiple rows here. Use COUNT(DISTINCT GCID) for active depositor counts."
            ],
            "enable_format_assistance": true
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "identifier": "main.money_stg.vw_ftd",
        "description": [
          "This table is the \"Single Source of Truth\" for First Time Deposits (FTD). A Global FTD is triggered the moment a customer makes their very first deposit to the company, regardless of which specific platform or AccountType they use. Use this table to measure new customer acquisition value, conversion dates, and initial funding sources. Each row represents one unique customer's initial conversion event."
        ],
        "column_configs": [
          {
            "column_name": "AccountTypeName",
            "description": [
              "The specific platform or account category (e.g., IBAN, Trading,) where the deposit was made. While the FTD is \"Global,\" this column identifies the entry point platform."
            ],
            "enable_format_assistance": true,
            "enable_entity_matching": true
          },
          {
            "column_name": "AmountInUsd",
            "description": [
              "The total gross deposited amount converted to USD at the time of the transaction. Use this to calculate \"Initial Deposit Value\" (IDV)."
            ],
            "enable_format_assistance": true
          },
          {
            "column_name": "Country",
            "description": [
              "The customer's country of residence at the time of the deposit. Use for geographical performance and regional conversion analysis."
            ]
          },
          {
            "column_name": "FtdDate",
            "description": [
