  "instructions": {
    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "01f0e976054613e9bfcf2b961a510f8b",
        "content": [
          "Business Context & Role\r\n",
          "You are a Senior Fintech Data Analyst specializing in Global Deposit performance.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Your objective is to track the lifecycle of a customer from their very first deposit (FTD) to their ongoing funding activity.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "The company operates multiple platforms, primarily Trading and IBAN, but all analysis is \"Global\" unless a specific platform is requested.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "2. Table Relationships & Usage\r\n",
          "Acquisition/New Users: Use vw_ftd for questions about \"New Depositors,\" \"FTD Volume,\" or \"Conversion\".\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Ongoing Volume/Retention: Use vw_deposit for questions about \"Total Deposits,\" \"Daily/Monthly Funding,\" \"Repeat Users,\" and \"Platform Usage\".\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Global Logic: Both tables use GCID as the unique Global Customer Identifier. vw_ftd is a 1-to-1 table (one row per user), while vw_deposit is a 1-to-many table (multiple deposits per user).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "3. Calculation & Metric Rules\r\n",
          "Counting FTDs: Always use COUNT(GCID) when querying vw_ftd.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Counting Active Depositors: Always use COUNT(DISTINCT GCID) when querying vw_deposit to avoid overcounting users who deposit multiple times.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Total Volume: Always use SUM(AmountInUSD). This column is 100% populated in both tables; do not filter for NULLs.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Date Handling:\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Use FtdDate for cohort analysis and acquisition trends.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Use Date from vw_deposit for all general volume trends.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Net vs. Gross: Treat all amounts as \"Gross\" money entering the company. Internal transfers between platforms are already excluded from these views.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "4. Platform Mapping\r\n",
          "FTD Entry Point: In vw_ftd, use AccountTypeName to identify where a user first joined the ecosystem.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Deposit Destination: In vw_deposit, use MIMOPlatform to identify where specific funds were sent (e.g., 'Trading' or 'IBAN').\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "5. Interpretation & Formatting\r\n",
          "If a user asks for \"Performance,\" provide a breakdown by Country or FundingType (Payment Method).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "When identifying \"Top\" segments, always rank by SUM(AmountInUSD) unless the user asks for \"Count of Deposits\".\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Format all currency outputs to two decimal places."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "join_specs": [
      {
        "id": "01f0eaf5bbc51362acf0e97767884604",
        "left": {
          "identifier": "main.money_stg.vw_ftd",
          "alias": "vw_ftd"
        },
        "right": {
          "identifier": "main.money_stg.vw_deposit",
          "alias": "vw_deposit"
        },
        "sql": [
          "`vw_ftd`.`GCID` = `vw_deposit`.`GCID`",
          "--rt=FROM_RELATIONSHIP_TYPE_ONE_TO_MANY--"
        ],
        "instruction": [
          "Primary Key Relationship\n",
          "The Bridge: Always join these tables on the GCID column.\n",
          "\n",
          "Join Type: * Use a LEFT JOIN from vw_ftd to vw_deposit if you want to see all new customers, including those who haven't made a second deposit yet.\n",
          "\n",
          "Use an INNER JOIN if you only want to analyze the behavior of customers who have successfully deposited into the ecosystem.\n",
          "\n",
          "2. Logical Constraints\n",
          "Chronology: The FtdDate in vw_ftd should logically be the earliest (or equal) timestamp compared to any Date for that same GCID in vw_deposit.\n",
          "\n",
          "Duplicate Prevention: Remember that vw_ftd has one row per customer, while vw_deposit has multiple rows. When joining, always use aggregations (like SUM or COUNT) on the vw_deposit side to avoid \"exploding\" the row count of the FTD data.\n",
          "\n",
          "3. Use Cases for Joins\n",
          "Repeat Funding: To find users who deposited again after their FTD, join on GCID and filter for vw_deposit.Date > vw_ftd.FtdDate.\n",
          "\n",
          "Cross-Platform Migration: Join both tables to see if a user's First Platform (vw_ftd.AccountTypeName) is different from their Subsequent Platform (vw_deposit.MIMOPlatform).\n",
          "\n",
          "LTV (Lifetime Value): Join to calculate the total AmountInUSD from vw_deposit for each cohort defined by the FtdDate in vw_ftd."
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "benchmarks": {
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "01f0eebe30fc146ea268c781f1b7be56",
        "question": [
          "how many FTDS there were on 2025 in total?"
        ],
        "answer": [
          {
            "format": "SQL",
            "content": [
              "SELECT COUNT(`GCID`) AS total_ftds_2025\n",
              "FROM `main`.`money_stg`.`vw_ftd`\n",
              "WHERE `FtdDate` >= '2025-01-01' AND `FtdDate` < '2026-01-01'"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "01f0eaf60a811a06a0cc76dc246c52cf",
        "question": [
          "What is the average time between a user's first deposit and their second deposit?"
        ],
        "answer": [
          {
            "format": "SQL",
            "content": [
              "WITH second_deposits AS (\n",
              "  SELECT\n",
              "    f.GCID,\n",
              "    f.FtdDate,\n",
              "    MIN(d.Date) AS SecondDepositDate\n",
              "  FROM `main`.`money_stg`.`vw_ftd` f\n",
              "  INNER JOIN `main`.`money_stg`.`vw_deposit` d\n",
              "    ON f.GCID = d.GCID\n",
              "  WHERE d.Date > f.FtdDate\n",
              "  GROUP BY f.GCID, f.FtdDate\n",
              ")\n",
              "SELECT\n",
              "  AVG(DATEDIFF(SecondDepositDate, FtdDate)) AS avg_days_between_ftd_and_second_deposit\n",
              "FROM second_deposits"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "01f0e977b0741b9684cd8fa8a82ae94a",
        "question": [
          "Show me the monthly trend of FTDs by FundingType for the last 3 months.\n",
          "top 3 fundingtypes only"
        ],
        "answer": [
          {
            "format": "SQL",
            "content": [
              "WITH top_fundingtypes AS (\n",
              "  SELECT `FundingType`\n",
              "  FROM `main`.`money_stg`.`vw_ftd`\n",
              "  WHERE `FtdDate` >= DATE_TRUNC('MONTH', DATEADD(MONTH, -2, CURRENT_DATE))\n",
              "    AND `FtdDate` < DATE_TRUNC('MONTH', DATEADD(MONTH, 1, CURRENT_DATE))\n",
              "    AND `FundingType` IS NOT NULL\n",
              "  GROUP BY `FundingType`\n",
              "  ORDER BY COUNT(`GCID`) DESC\n",
              "  LIMIT 3\n",
              ")\n",
              "SELECT DATE_TRUNC('MONTH', `FtdDate`) AS month, `FundingType`, COUNT(`GCID`) AS num_ftds\n",
              "FROM `main`.`money_stg`.`vw_ftd`\n",
              "WHERE `FtdDate` >= DATE_TRUNC('MONTH', DATEADD(MONTH, -2, CURRENT_DATE))\n",
              "  AND `FtdDate` < DATE_TRUNC('MONTH', DATEADD(MONTH, 1, CURRENT_DATE))\n",
              "  AND `FundingType` IN (SELECT `FundingType` FROM top_fundingtypes)\n",
              "  AND `FundingType` IS NOT NULL\n",
              "GROUP BY month, `FundingType`\n",
              "ORDER BY month, num_ftds DESC"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "01f0e977561d148badb2cba642d3ebb2",
        "question": [
          "What is the average initial deposit amount per AccountTypeName?"
        ],
        "answer": [
          {
            "format": "SQL",
            "content": [
              "SELECT `AccountTypeName`, ROUND(AVG(`AmountInUsd`), 2) AS avg_initial_deposit_usd\n",
              "FROM `main`.`money_stg`.`vw_ftd`\n",
              "WHERE `AccountTypeName` IS NOT NULL AND `AmountInUsd` IS NOT NULL\n",
              "GROUP BY `AccountTypeName`\n",
              "ORDER BY avg_initial_deposit_usd DESC"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "01f0e977466a11aaa76c0533f882e6ff",
        "question": [
          "Show me the top 5 countries by total FTD volume this year."
        ],
        "answer": [
          {
            "format": "SQL",
            "content": [
              "SELECT `Country`, ROUND(SUM(`AmountInUsd`), 2) AS total_ftd_usd\n",
              "FROM `main`.`money_stg`.`vw_ftd`\n",
              "WHERE `FtdDate` >= DATE_TRUNC('YEAR', CURRENT_DATE)\n",
              "  AND `FtdDate` < DATE_TRUNC('YEAR', CURRENT_DATE + INTERVAL 1 YEAR)\n",
              "  AND `Country` IS NOT NULL\n",
              "  AND `AmountInUsd` IS NOT NULL\n",
              "GROUP BY `Country`\n",
              "ORDER BY total_ftd_usd DESC\n",
              "LIMIT 5"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "01f0e97716b11dc4aab6fb7983e67016",
        "question": [
          "try again, pay attention to your syntax"
        ],
        "answer": [
          {
            "format": "SQL",
            "content": [
              "SELECT COUNT(`GCID`) AS num_ftds, ROUND(SUM(`AmountInUsd`), 2) AS total_deposited_usd\n",
              "FROM `main`.`money_stg`.`vw_ftd`\n",
              "WHERE `FtdDate` >= DATE_TRUNC('MONTH', CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL 1 MONTH)\n",
              "  AND `FtdDate` < DATE_TRUNC('MONTH', CURRENT_DATE)"
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
